  "description": "<i>Firestorm</i> is a top-down shooter, but the game requires a bit of thinking. The titular hero is able to create destructive fire-balls, control computer memory banks and move inanimate objects with the power of telekinesis. He must rescue his girlfriend, who is imprisoned in criminal organization's citadel. This citadel is a big maze, and the game has 12 levels.<br><br>Firestorm goes through citadel as you fight against enemies and avoid others obstacles like floor sweeps and &quot;derezzers&quot; (pyramid type columns in corridors).",
